advisor.extraInfo: Sorry if I answered the earlier questions incorrectly but I wanted to clarify my answers. I am just finishing up an integrated Master's at University College London and will start a MRes + PhD in Cardiovascular Research at Cambridge later this year. I think I could be a great addition to your team because I come from low income background and am a first generation university student. I've got some experience of working in outreach projects through UCL Careers Extra and the First Gen Society and would love to contribute to your work. Best of all, I got into Cambridge with a low 2.1 so I think I can demystify the notion that you have to be a top student to get a place at the best universities (I am usually in the bottom 10 of my ~110 cohort). Looking forward to working with you soon!
